vivint  wikipedia vivint from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search vivint inc type private industry security systems fire detection home automation photovoltaics founded  as apx alarm security solutions inc founder todd pedersen keith nellesen headquarters provo utah key people todd pedersen ceo alex dunn president number of employees  website wwwvivintcom the thermostat controls on the vivint app for iphone vivint inc formerly known as apx alarm security solutions inc is a private smart home services provider in the united states and canada in  the blackstone group acquired vivint for more than  billion as of august  vivint had more than one million customers in the us and canada vivint is listed on the forbes list of america’s best employers” and was also named one of forbes’ “most promising companies” in  contents  history  products and services  vivint solar  awards  philanthropy  legal issues  references  external links historyedit in  keith nellesen and todd pedersen cofounded apx alarm security solutions in provo utah at the time the company sold and installed security systems vivint began retaining customers in  after it became a home monitoring provider the company expanded its service to canada that year after signing a  million credit facility agreement with goldman sachs goldman sachs and apx alarm completed another credit facility agreement worth  million in  that november the company acquired a central alarm monitoring station from criticom monitoring services a subsidiary of protection one in st paul minnesota apx alarm opened a new corporate headquarters in provo utah a month later apx alarm security solutions rebranded as vivint in february  the company completed a  million senior debt financing led by goldman sachs that month vivint also received funding from peterson partners and jupiter partners the company launched vivint solar a solar energy company in  the company partnered with alarmcom early that year to deploy severe weather alerts to their customer base vivint was acquired by the blackstone group in september  in  forbes ranked the company th in its annual ranking of americas most promising companies vivint acquired smartrove a wireless mesh networking technology provider and began wireless broadband in august  in october inc named the company the second most job creating private company in the united states in  the company created the vivint fellows program a summer internship program at the vivint innovation center vivint acquired the cloud storage startup space monkey a company founded by clint gordoncarroll and alen peacock in  vivint ceo todd pedersen appeared on the season finale of the cbs television show undercover boss in february  the company opened a new monitoring center in eagan minnesota in august  on october   vivint acquired the naming rights to the utah jazzs home arena renaming the building as vivint smart home arena the contract will last for  years peter thiel and solamere capital coled a  million investment in vivint in april  solamere strategic investors include hewlett packard enterprise ceo meg whitman sun microsystems cofounder scott mcnealy and former walmart ceo h lee scott jr products and servicesedit the vivint skycontrol touchscreen smart home hub vivint launched its own cloudbased smart home solution in june  the system provides a centralized control a smartphone application for remote access and learning algorithms that automatically pick up on a users patterns in  the touchscreen vivint skycontrol panel received a ce pro best award for new custom electronic products introduced in  in  vivint introduced the vivint doorbell camera to its smart home solution the product allows consumers to see hear and speak with visitors on their doorstep from any mobile device the product received a  electronic house product of the year award in january  vivint announced partnerships with amazon and nest vivint also announced vivint element its own smart thermostat and the vivint ping camera the first indoor camera with onetouch call out vivint solaredit in  vivint inc launched a standalone company vivint solar as a solar electricity provider that designs installs and maintains residential photovoltaic systems the company offers solar panels via a power purchase agreement ppa vivint solar owns installs and maintains solar panels on customers’ homes in exchange for customers agreeing to purchase the solar energy their panels produce customers do not pay for installation but pay for energy that the panels produce for the life of the contracts vivint solar is similar to other alternative solar companies like solarcity sunrun and sungevity its innovation in the field is the use of microinverters for each separate solar panel allowing maximum production when some of the panels are in the shade in october  vivint solar made its initial public offering on the new york stock exchange under the ticker symbol vslr in july  sunedison announced plans to purchase vivint solar for  billion this deal subsequently fell through and vivint solar has initiated suit against sunedison for breach of contract with sunedison filing for chapter  bankruptcy reorganization awardsedit forbes list of america’s best employers vivint is one of  companies in the us to make the inaugural forbes list of “america’s best employers” vivint is also the topranked security and home automation company on the list and was named to forbes list of “america’s most promising companies” in  vivint is the  recipient of the women’s choice award for america’s best home security system best contact centers in the world vivints customer solutions manager matt hansen won the silver award for best use of social media in a contact center from the global contact center the stevie awards selected vivint as the customer service department of the year from more than  organizations of all sizes and in virtually every industry vivint won a  inc hire power award from inc magazine ranking at  on the publication’s list of winners inc magazine also named vivint the  jobcreating company in consumer products and services and the  job creator in utah pcmag named vivint sky one of the best products of the year in  consumers digest rated vivint a “best buy” in  vivint won two gold stevie awards and two silver stevie awards for customer service in  vivint smart home was the overall winner of the business intelligence group’s inaugural best places to work award contest philanthropyedit the vivint gives back focuses on helping children with intellectual disabilities through intelligent products and services vivint employees and owners contribute time money and volunteer hours to perform services for these children in  vivint gives back foundation was named the “corporate volunteer program of the year”  in april  vivint employees worked with the feed my starving children organization to donate  and assemble  meal kits to feed children in haiti vivint has donated a total of  meals enough to feed more than  children for an entire year in  vivint became the official safety sponsor for autism speaks the nation’s largest autism organization vivint employees volunteer time and money to renovate homes for families who have children with intellectual disabilities employees install vivint smart home technology in the homes and sensory rooms with developmental components such as swings rockclimbing walls reading nooks and art stations since its creation in  vivint gives back has donated  million and more than  service hours in february  the company donated  million to the utah valley university to establish a professional sales program as well as a smart lab for marketing research legal issuesedit from  through  the company settled with the states of arkansas oregon wisconsin and contra costa county california and agreed to conform its contracts to refrain from certain sales practices in  the company settled for  with the kansas attorney general which accused sales agents of using deceptive practices while going doortodoor offering to install or replace home security systems the agents also allegedly failed to advise the consumers of their rights under the kansas consumer protection act and did not disclose all costs associated with switching alarm system providers the ohio attorney general settled with vivint in  following complaints alleging deceptive sales practices and the companys refusal to honor cancellation notices vivint agreed to comply with ohio consumer laws and paid  in fines also in  vivint agreed to an assurance of voluntary compliance in nebraska the company promised not to make any misrepresentations while engaging in sales the company also donated  to two charities in lancaster county nebraska as of  two federal classaction lawsuits were filed against vivint for alleged violations of the tcpa in june  vivint agreed to a proposed settlement in benzion which included a  million settlement fund referencesedit  mark dawson june   city business secures huge us linked deal retrieved october     vivint rapidly automating canadian homes security systems news  retrieved    apx alarm security solutions inc increases credit facility to  million business wire  retrieved    a b wang ucilia october   home security firm enters solar market with m fund forbes   blackstone buys security firm vivint for over  billion september   retrieved october     press release  apx group holdings inc reports second quarter  results business wire retrieved  september    nancy blair june   vivint sky promises easy home automation retrieved october     a b forbes company profile  vivint forbes retrieved  june    a b c d antone gonsalves april   to sell home automation vivint needs ‘some aggressiveness’ retrieved october     mochari ilan  november  move over silicon valley utah has arrived inc retrieved  march    a b c vivint sheds light on its marketing methods june   retrieved october     apx alarm opens second central monitor station business 