er inc named the company the second most job creating private company in the united states in  the company created the vivint fellows program a summer internship program at the vivint innovation center vivint acquired the cloud storage startup space monkey a company founded by clint gordoncarroll and alen peacock in  vivint ceo todd pedersen appeared on the season finale of the cbs television show undercover boss in february  the company opened a new monitoring center in eagan minnesota in august  on october   vivint acquired the naming rights to the utah jazzs home arena renaming the building as vivint smart home arena the contract will last for  years peter thiel and solamere capital coled a  million investment in vivint in april  solamere strategic investors include hewlett packard enterprise ceo meg whitman sun microsystems cofounder scott mcnealy and former walmart ceo h lee scott jr products and servicesedit the vivint skycontrol touchscreen smart home hub vivint launched its own cloudbased smart home solution in june  the system provides a centralized control a smartphone application for remote access and learning algorithms that automatically pick up on a users patterns in  the touchscreen vivint skycontrol panel received a ce pro best award for new custom electronic products introduced in  in  vivint introduced the vivint doorbell camera to its smart home solution the product allows consumers to see hear and speak with visitors on their doorstep from any mobile device the product received a  electronic house product of the year award in january  vivint announced partnerships with amazon and nest vivint also announced vivint element its own smart thermostat and the vivint ping camera the first indoor camera with onetouch call out vivint solaredit in  vivint inc launched a standalone company vivint solar as a solar electricity provider that designs installs and maintains residential photovoltaic systems the company offers solar panels via a power purchase agreement ppa vivint solar owns installs and maintains solar panels on customers’ homes in exchange for customers agreeing to purchase the solar energy their panels produce customers do not pay for installation but pay for energy that the panels produce for the life of the contracts vivint solar is similar to other alternative solar companies like solarcity sunrun and sungevity its innovation in the field is the use of microinverters for each separate solar panel allowing maximum production when some of the panels are in the shade in october  vivint solar made its initial public offering on the new york stock exchange under the ticker symbol vslr in july  sunedison announced plans to purchase vivint solar for  billion this deal subsequently fell through and vivint solar has initiated suit against sunedison for breach of contract with sunedison filing for chapter  bankruptcy reorganization awardsedit forbes list of america’s best employers vivint is one of  companies in the us to make the inaugural forbes list of “america’s best employers” vivint is also the topranked security and home automation company on the list and was named to forbes list of “america’s most promising companies” in  vivint is the  recipient of the women’s choice award for america’s best home security system best contact centers in the world vivints customer solutions manager matt hansen won the silver award for best use of social media in a contact center from the global contact center the stevie awards selected vivint as the customer service department of the year from more than  organizations of all sizes and in virtually every industry vivint won a  inc hire power award from inc magazine ranking at  on the publication’s list of winners inc magazine also named vivint the  jobcreating company in consumer products and services and the  job creator in utah pcmag named vivint sky one of the best products of the year in  consumers digest rated vivint a “best buy” in  vivint won two gold stevie awards 